Mr Charles Dickens presents his compliments to Mr Montgomerie, and begs to thank him for his obliging letter.<note>Montgomerie had written to CD, offering a correction to John Capper's article entitled "Underwriting", concerning the Society of Underwriters or Marine Insurers, commonly known as Lloyd's (<hi rend="italic">Household Words</hi> 5 [4 Sept 1852]: 585-9).</note> He has looked into the authorities again, and availed himself of Mr Montgomerie's correction.<note>The correction was printed as "Lloyd's List", in <hi rend="italic">Household Words</hi> 6 (2 Oct 1852): 69-70; it altered the date of the earliest list in existence from 1745 to 1740.</note>
